---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout title="About | Farooq Qureshi" description="About Farooq Qureshi">
  <main>
    <article class="space-y-6 text-sm leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-medium text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mt-8 first:mt-0">Short</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p>Hi, I'm Farooq.</p>
        <p>
          I study <a href="https://www.uoee.rocks/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Electrical Engineering</a> at <a href="https://uottawa.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The University of Ottawa</a>.
          This summer, I'm working at <a href="https://www.fleetway.ca/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fleetway</a> as a Junior Electrical Engineer.
        </p>
        <p>
          I previously led the team behind <a href="https://2026.uottahack.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">uOttaHack</a>, the largest technology event in Ottawa.
        </p>
        <p>
          In my free time I teach competitive debating, <a href="/other/books">read</a> and <a href="/writing">write</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Please feel free to say <a href="mailto:farooq.qureshi@outlook.com">hi</a>, see my <a href="https://github.com/farooqqureshii" target="_blank" rel="noopener">code</a>, browse my <a href="https://curius.app/farooq-qureshi" target="_blank" rel="noopener">interests</a>, or view my <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/farooqq" target="_blank" rel="noopener">experience</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-sm font-medium text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mt-8">Long</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
      <p>
        I was born in Karachi, Pakistan. I spent a small chunk of my childhood there, and then came to Canada where I lived in Toronto and then Calgary. Most of my education was done in Calgary. I moved to Ottawa in 2024.
      </p>
      <p>
        Academically, my current interests lie at the intersection between system analysis and signal processing. Namely, the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fast_Fourier_transform" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fast Fourier Transform</a> (in particular, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rader%27s_FFT_algorithm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Rader's Algorithm</a>), the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Z-transform" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Z-Transform</a> and the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nyquist_stability_criterion" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nyquist Stability Criterion</a>. Professionally, I'm interested in product and strategy.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before University, I spent almost all of high school competitively debating, where I won at Stanford's Invitational and Harvard's Invitational Tournaments. I also participated in Model UN, where I competed at conferences across the nation, and also organized the largest high-school Model UN conference in Western Canada.
      </p>
      <p>
        I now am lucky enough to coach some exceptionally bright students in both these areas. I've coached the winners of the Alberta Provincial Debating Championships, Canadian National Debating Championships, Harvard Invitationals & Yale Invitationals.
      </p>
      <p>
        A long-term aspiration of mine is to understand abstract art more. In the short-term, I'm trying to read more biographies.
      </p>
      <p>
        The traits I admire the most are altruism and intellectual humility, a trait that I try to avoid is inflexibility. My favorite author is a tie between Ernest Hemingway and Prabda Yoon. Favorite book (changes far too often) but is currently To the Lighthouse by Virginia Woolf. Favorite movie is also a tie between Frances Ha and Green Book. Favorite music is from Jelani Aryeh or Vince Staples.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm always extremely interested in talking about the above, or anything else. Please feel free to <a href="mailto:farooq.qureshi@outlook.com">email me</a>.
      </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
